				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				okay, to find out how good a item is, its really simple ppl. delay = how many times a wepon is swung in a round. SO, matmatically. you take the delay and divide it into one round and multiply by its damage. simple.<BR>
if you are dual weilding then you add the second's weapons damage rating &lt;for all those that think a Double Lange's is better than 2 singles LOL u are sadly mistaken&gt;<BR>
<BR>
Damage rating =     1 / .(delay)    x damage<BR>
<BR>
so, GZ is (1 / .39) * 18 = 46.15<BR>
    LG is (1 / .44) * 19 = 43.18<BR>
however, you also have the stat increases on LG<BR>
in my opinion they are equal to LG being better (5)dex = maybe one more hit, and the STR modifier makes LG hit closer to maximum damage.<BR>
 and ppl, the single lange's axe is 6 dam in 23<BR>
 thats TWO of 6 damage in 23 delay = 12 dam in 23<BR>
 12 in 23 delay kick ***<BR>
 damage rating of the lange's is<BR>
(1 / .23) * 6 = 26 damage rating,&lt;awesome for1hnd&gt;<BR>
dual wielding, you have 52 damage rating.<BR>
comparatively (1 / .35) * 8 for the screamer is 22<BR>
hope you all understand this formula is based on basics, you level/class may affect this &lt;thus, no dual weild&gt;<BR>
the higher damage rating the more efficient you are.<BR>
<BR>
Formula =   ( 1 Rnd divided by .delay &lt;44 delay = .44&gt; multiply the result by ur damage)<BR>
<BR>
delay is how long before you can swing your wepon in ONE round, so a 50 delay = 2 swings in a round<BR>
<BR>
(1 / . delay) = how many times u can swing it in a round, multiply that by ur damage and u have ur wepons effective damage a single ROUND
				</font>
